 Monday, August 23, 2004 				 Heckler fired
				 	 George W. Bush Charleston (West Virginia)  Aug. 22 (AP): A man who heckled President George W.  Bush at a political rally was fired from his job at an advertising  and design company for offending a client who provided tickets  to the event.																								The fired graphic designer yesterday said he wont try to get his job back. 																								Im mad less about losing the job. Im more mad about the reasons, said Glen Hiller, 35. All I did was show up and voice my opinion.																								Hiller was ushered out of Hedgesville High School on Tuesday after shouting his disagreement with Bushs comments about the war in Iraq war. 																								He surrounds himself with people who support him, Hiller said of Bush. 
